                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Calhoun</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Knox informs Mr. Calhoun that the following telegram has to-day been sent to
                    the American embassy at St. Petersburg:<note n="1" xml:id="d238fn1">Telegram of
                        Apr. 18 supra.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Mr. Knox states that Mr. Calhoun may read this telegram to the minister for
                    foreign affairs for his information. Directs that the telegram be repeated to
                    the American embassy at Tokyo.</p>
            </div>
